-- Reduction in Brazil Debt Load Could Mean `Faster Rating Upgrade,' S&P Says
-- B y   I u r i   D a n t a s
-- 2010-11-03T20:25:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/reduction-in-brazil-debt-load-could-mean-faster-rating-upgrade-s-p-says.html
Brazil’s efforts to reduce the amount
of outstanding debt could result in a “faster rating upgrade,”
said Sebastian Briozzo, a Latin America director at Standard &
Poor’s.  An improvement in Brazil’s fiscal situation is “very
important” to the country’s rating, Briozzo said in telephone
interview from Buenos Aires.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Iuri Dantas in Brasilia at 
